comment_data.body: After messing with different configurations, it seems like turning on 'Replace the Run and Debug console output with an experimental Flutter Logging view' causes this.

Any updates on this? I'm running on Flutter plugin 28.0.1 and the issue is still there.

@xster you mention the experimental Flutter logging view is the problem. How/where can this be disabled?

Sorry to have missed this the first time around!

> After messing with different configurations, it seems like turning on 'Replace the Run and Debug console output with an experimental Flutter Logging view' causes this.

It's really surprising that disabling the logging view did the trick.  It should really not have any way to pollute a simulator run.  I'll do some digging though in case I'm overlooking something.

> How/where can this be disabled?

@bizz84 : that view gets enabled/disabled in your IntelliJ preferences.  (Note that it's off by default.)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67586/46017490-78d54f80-c08c-11e8-9eb3-20a7ee92af5e.png)

Please do report back if this resolves your issue.

Thanks!

I still get the problem, with or without the experimental view enabled.

![flutter-conf](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/153167/46018558-0e470280-c0d2-11e8-848c-f7089bc6c000.png)

Oddly enough this issue appears to happen on Xcode 9.4.1, but not on Xcode 10.

Xcode 10 with the latest flutter dev channel seems to work fine for me:
